Say hello to your new go-to noodle snack: the ramelette 😏⁣
⁣
This is what happens when we combine two of our favorite things: Saucy Noodles and omelettes 🤯 ⁣
⁣
The noodles crisp up on the bottom, while the inside stays fluffy, thanks to the whisked egg 🍳⁣
⁣
Here’s how to make it 👇🏽⁣
⁣
Chili Sesame Saucy Noodles⁣
3 eggs⁣
1 Tbsp Greek yogurt⁣
1 tsp neutral oil⁣
1 Tbsp. chili crisp⁣
1 slice American cheese⁣
1 sausage, cooked⁣
Mayo for garnish⁣
Tonkatsu sauce (or sriracha) for garnish⁣
Furikake for garnish ⁣
⁣
1. Cook Chili Sesame Saucy Noodles, and set them aside.⁣
2. In a small bowl, whisk together eggs and Greek yogurt. ⁣
3. In a large nonstick pan over medium-high heat, add the oil until hot. Then, spread the Saucy Noodles evenly and cook until the noodles get slightly crispy.⁣
4. Pour the prepared egg mixture all over the noodles, then place chili crisp, cheese, and sausage. ⁣
5. Cook for 2 to 3 minutes, or until the eggs are set around the edges. Fold it in half, and cook for a minute or so.⁣
6. Garnish with mayo, tonkatsu sauce (or sriracha sauce), and furikake.⁣
⁣
#easyrecipes #noodles #snackideas

No more soggy crumbles — here's our no-press hack for getting perfectly crispy tofu! 💥

🔪 Slice tofu into ¼-inch planks.
♨️ Bring 4 cups water + 1/4 cup of salt to a boil in a small pot.
💦 Once boiling, turn off heat, add tofu, + soak for 10 minutes.
🧻 Remove tofu + pat dry with paper towels. Dice into cubes. 

You're ready to pan fry! Go get that crisp bb 🔥

• SCHEMAS OF PLAY • 

Like this reel ♥️ and comment SCHEMAS and I’ll send a link to your DM’s for you to receive a downloadable doc all about the schemas of play! 🔗
.
Schemas are a pattern of behaviour that you might notice in your child’s play - like lining objects up in a line, or dumping out tubs of toys - that repeats itself across many areas of play. Schemas are not developmental or ‘fixed’ - two children of different ages may be working within the same schema, and a particular schema may be observed for weeks, months or even years. The different play schemas are:
Orientation 
Positioning 
Scattering 
Enclosure 
Trajectory 
Enveloping 
Connecting 
Transporting 
Rotating 
Transforming 
.
My document gives a run down on each one and examples of the types of activities you can try if you observe these patterns of play in your child! 
.
.

• GRACE AND COURTESY WITH YOUR BIGS • 

Like 🫶 and comment MANNERS and I’ll send the link to your DMs 🔗 

As my two bigs are getting bigger, I’m finding a lot of new situations popping up where some explicit explanations/practise are helpful for them to understand more complex situations and contexts. Situations which require ‘manners’ or ‘courtesy’ in particular, for example manners around being served food that they don’t like, or introducing yourself to new friends, or not staring when they seem someone who looks different from themselves. 

This flipbook was recommended to me by a friend and it’s now become our dinnertime conversation starter. I flip through it if there’s anything in particular I’m feeling we need to cover, and it provokes great discussions without being directed at any particular child, meaning we cover these topics from a joint place of curiosity rather than from a place of critique. 

It gives a short, sharp, easy to understand explanations that make tricky topics easy to talk about and easy for kids to understand, and has been a really valuable tool to have in our home to help cover grace and courtesy with our young children!

People ask me what it’s like to homeschool four kids, and I don’t know how to explain that it’s really just living our lives alongside each other. It’s not something we slot into every day, it IS every day. It’s not one part of our life, it IS our life. It’s not a neat little box I can tick, it’s a beautiful mess of ideas and experiences, that we come out the other side of having grown and changed and learned things without being able to pinpoint the exact moment that any of it happened. 
There’s no set of steps, no secret recipe, except letting go of the idea that there’s anything else we ‘should’ be doing that’s more valuable. There’s nothing more valuable to me than building strong relationships with my kids, and to give them time to build strong relationships with themselves and each other 🩷 I hope they remember their childhood with nothing but love, just like I will.

PS. Hi 👋🏻 we’re back on the gram 😆 if you’ve been with us a while, thank you for still being here ☺️ and if you’ve never seen us before, I’m Emma! I was a primary school and early childhood teacher and now I’m a stay at home mum/homeschooling mum to my four girls. We live in Brisbane and love life 🫶🏻 I’m all about play and following my kids interests and natural development 🌱

• DIY CHRISTMAS SNOW GLOBES • 

Like ❤️ and Comment SNOWGLOBE (one word!) and I’ll dm you the links to the things we used 
. 
These are the easiest little DIY’s to do with your kids, and are a fun joint holiday project for 3 years + 🎄
.
They would also make cute Christmas gifts for friends or family! 
.
How to:
- Use hot glue to glue a figurine to the base/lid of the globe. Make sure your figurine isn’t too small/flat or you won’t be able to see it once the water is in the globe. You can use a plastic block to raise the figurine if needed, by gluing a plastic block/part (such as a bottle cap, mini container etc) to the base and then gluing the figurine on top. We used the clear containers left from the glitter we poured into the snow globes to raise the smaller figures so they could be seen! 
- Fill the globe with water (almost to the top, you need a small amount of space so it shakes up properly) 
- Tip glitter flakes/sparkles into the water, along with a small amount of glycerine (around 1-2 teaspoons, you can add more after if the glitter is falling too quickly, the glycerine slows down the glitter falling to give the ‘snow’ effect)
- Screw the lid on so that the figurine is immersed in the water. Tighten.
- Shake it up and watch the glitter fall like snow! You can add more glitter or glycerine as needed, until you are happy with the result ❄️ 
.
You can also hot glue the lid on at the end if you wish (I didn’t do this as I wanted to be able to remove the lid to add more glitter if needed)
.
.

💡 Tax Season Legal Tip

 Did you know that most personal injury settlements are not taxable?

If you received compensation for physical injuries or illness, the IRS typically does not treat that money as income. That means your settlement—meant to cover pain, suffering, and recovery—is not something you owe taxes on.

✅ No taxes on your justice
✅ No taxes on your healing

You are being made WHOLE again, not profiting.

It’s one of the few areas where the law and fairness align. As always, check with your legal or tax advisor—but know your rights this tax season.

All three of these answers are actually correct!
A will takes effect after death, detailing asset distribution, while a living will guides decisions during incapacitation.

A living will focuses on healthcare preferences, unlike a will, which doesn’t cover medical decisions.

In a will, you appoint an executor for estate management; a living will allows you to express your wishes regarding life-sustaining treatment.

Both documents serve crucial, yet distinct roles in ensuring your wishes are honored. Enlightening, right? Let’s embrace these tools to secure our futures comprehensively. 📜 💡 

....

¡Las tres respuestas son correctas!
Un testamento entra en vigor después del fallecimiento y detalla la distribución de los bienes, mientras que un testamento vital guía las decisiones durante la incapacidad.

Un testamento vital se centra en las preferencias de atención médica, a diferencia de un testamento, que no abarca las decisiones médicas.

En un testamento, usted nombra a un albacea para la administración del patrimonio; un testamento vital le permite expresar sus deseos con respecto al tratamiento para el soporte vital.

Ambos documentos cumplen funciones cruciales, aunque distintas, para garantizar que sus deseos se cumplan. Esclarecedor, ¿verdad? Aprovechemos estas herramientas para asegurar nuestro futuro de forma integral. 📜 💡

Separating from your spouse doesn't automatically revoke your will. In most states, a will stays valid until legally changed or revoked, no matter the marital status updates. 💍 🔄 However, divorce can change the terms of your will. 📜 💔 Often, the law may treat a divorced spouse as if they predeceased the will maker, removing them from the will. However, this does not apply to mere separation. Remember to update your will and other estate planning documents if you separate or divorce to mirror your current wishes. ✍️ Laws vary by region, so consulting an estate planning attorney in your area is key. 🔑 👩‍⚖️

....

Separarse de su cónyuge no revoca automáticamente su testamento. En la mayoría de los estados, un testamento sigue siendo válido hasta que se modifique o revoque legalmente, sin importar las actualizaciones del estado civil. 💍 🔄 Sin embargo, el divorcio puede cambiar los términos de su testamento. 📜 💔 A menudo, la ley puede tratar a un cónyuge divorciado como si hubiera fallecido antes que el testador, eliminándolo del testamento. Sin embargo, esto no se aplica a la mera separación. Recuerde actualizar su testamento y otros documentos de planificación patrimonial si se separa o se divorcia para reflejar sus deseos actuales. ✍️ Las leyes varían según la región, por lo que consultar a un abogado de planificación patrimonial en su área es clave. 🔑 👩‍⚖️ 

#EstatePlanning #LifeChanges #LegalKnowledge

Naming a successor (or backup) trustee in your trust ensures seamless management of assets. 🔄 Life is unpredictable, and if your primary trustee is unable to serve due to unforeseen circumstances, having someone who can step in is crucial. A successor trustee can maintain the integrity and purpose of your trust without interruptions or legal hassles. 📜 This foresight protects your assets and beneficiaries, ensuring your wishes are honored. 

....

Nombrar un fideicomisario sucesor (o suplente) en su fideicomiso garantiza una gestión fluida de los activos. 🔄 La vida es impredecible y, si su fideicomisario principal no puede cumplir sus funciones debido a circunstancias imprevistas, es fundamental contar con alguien que pueda intervenir. Un fideicomisario sucesor puede mantener la integridad y el propósito de su fideicomiso sin interrupciones ni problemas legales. 📜 Esta previsión protege sus activos y beneficiarios, lo que garantiza que se respeten sus deseos.

Thinking you’ll save some money on estate planning by simply transferring ownership of your home to your adult child? 🏠 Think again. This move can backfire big time. Here are a few reasons why:

3. Your home becomes vulnerable to your child’s creditors, risking the roof over your head due to their financial troubles. 💔

Christmas time is here, and it's the season of giving! 🎁 But having the right strategy is important. Did you know you can make substantial, tax-free gifts to loved ones by using strategic gifting? Here’s how:

1️⃣ Annual Exclusion: Gift up to $18,000 per person per year with no gift tax. 
2️⃣ Lifetime Exemption: Use up to $13.61 million of lifetime exemptions to transfer wealth tax-free. 
3️⃣ Split Gifts: Married? Double up to give $36,000 per recipient if you're a married couple. 
4️⃣ Spread It Out: Consider spreading out your gift over multiple years to stay under the $18,000 per year limit. 
5️⃣ Direct Support: Payments for education or medical expenses go untaxed if paid directly to educational institutions or medical providers!

Estate planning helps you give thoughtfully, maximizing what you're able to leave behind for your loved ones. 📜 ✨

...

1️⃣ Exclusión anual: obsequia hasta $18,000 por persona por año sin impuestos sobre donaciones.

Chelsea Women have announced tech entrepreneur Alexis Ohanian has joined the club as a minority investor.

Ohanian, who is the husband of American tennis icon Serena Williams, has reportedly bought a stake in the club worth around £20 million and will have a seat on the board.

This comes a year after Chelsea restructured the club’s hierarchy to attract investors, specifically to support women’s football.

Ohanian was Angel City FC’s largest shareholder before the NWSL side was sold in 2024 for just under £200 million. The 42-year-old also founded social media platform Reddit and has an estimated net worth of $150 million.

Speaking on this new venture, he said: “I’ve bet big on women’s sports before, and I’m doing it again. I’m honoured for the chance to help this iconic club become every American’s favourite WSL team and much, much more.”

This move follows an ever-growing trend of big-name investors buying into the women’s game. Natalie Portman co-founded Angel City FC and is one of several high-profile owners heading up the franchise. NFL star Patrick Mahomes co-owns Kansas City Current with his wife, while Michelle Kang’s London City Lionesses have just been promoted to the WSL.

A judge has opened criminal proceedings against Real Madrid player Raul Asencio and three other former Real Madrid academy players in connection with the recording and distribution of s*xual images of two women. 

One of the girls was only 16 years old, with the suspects including Raul Asencio being 20 and 21 years old.

As of today, the girl suffers from post-traumatic stress resulting from what happened.

The formal indictment by a Spanish court means the case is moving towards a potential trial. The players are accused of charges that may include unlawful disclosure of secrets, violation of privacy, and potentially offenses related to the involvement of a minor.

Asencio has publicly addressed the allegations and denies significant involvement in the recording and distribution of the images.

According to Asencio, the court order suggests his potential involvement was limited to the "possible momentary viewing of some images by a third party," and it does not attribute to him any participation in their recording or dissemination. He has also stated that he was not the one who sent any intimate images or videos to third parties.

The attorney-client privilege is a rule that protects the confidentiality of communications between lawyers and clients. I had walked life’s path with an easy tread
Had followed where comfort and pleasure led;
And then one day in a quiet place
I met the Master, face to face.

With station and rank and wealth for a goal
Much thought for the body, but none for the soul;
I had thought to win in life’s mad race,
When I met the Master, face to face.

I had built my castles and reared them high,
Till their towers pierced the blue of the sky,
I had vowed to rule with an iron mace,
When I met the Master, face to face.

I met Him and knew Him, and blushed to see
That eyes full of sorrow were turned on me;
And I faltered, and fell at His feet that day,
While all my castles melted away.

Melted and vanished, and in their place
I saw nought else but my Master’s face;
And I cried aloud: “Oh, make me meet
To follow the path of Thy wounded feet.”

And now my thoughts are for the souls of men,
I’ve lost my life, to find it again.
E’er since that day in a quiet place
I met the Master, face to face.

An alarming piece of news has just come out for NRIs living in the US… and their families in India…

A new law has been proposed in the US by which any non citizen of the US sending any money outside of the US…

Would be charged a 5% tax on top of that remittance.

So all Indians living in the US who are not US citizens yet, and even those on a Green Card, would need to pay this extra 5% while sending money to India.

This tax will be collected by banks and money transfer agencies at the time of transfer.

For context on the scale of this issue, in FY 24, NRIs sent USD 32 Bn to India from the US…

Which means a USD 1.6 Bn annual tax on this if the Bill comes into effect.

The Bill is called the One Big Beautiful Bill, and once passed in around July, this tax may take effect.

India has a TCS mechanism on foreign payments too, where you get the tax credit later… but we don’t know how much of the tax credit would be allowed in this case.

If you’re an NRI in the US and need to send money to India, it may be best to do it before this law is enforced.

Do you know which countries benefit the most when there is a war in the world?

There are two ways to look at this...

The first kind of countries are those that are the world’s largest suppliers of defence equipment - it’s the US, Russia, China, Israel...

But the second type is most interesting... these are the neutral countries which don’t take sides, maintain absolute safety of its people, and become the place where the millionaires from war struck economies start transferring their wealth...

They have the highest reward to risk ratio in such uncertain times, and include Switzerland and Singapore... but the top of the list is Dubai in the UAE...

It’s a safe hub for capital and people... and benefited during the Iran-Iraq war, the Kuwait War, the America-Iraq war, and the Russia Ukraine war... 

And how they’ve enabled it is a masterclass on how small economies are run...

Since Dubai had practically no income from oil, it realized it was bang in the middle of Europe, Africa and Asia and thus, started luxury airlines like Emirates and Etihad to just give people free layovers on long flights.

So you have global travellers (the rich) stopping here, they realize they could set up trading companies with zero taxes...

So those companies started setting up... you need labour, which comes easy from Pakistan, Sri Lanka and African countries...

You need to get your family, you get a golden visa...

And when the rich start banking their international payments here, the money funds luxury real estate, luxury retail, and makes it a fabulous holiday home cum business destination for the wealthy.

Such that it has the highest density of millionaires in the world. Almost 70k millionaires for a population of just 3.5 Million!

And they very strategically peg their currency to the dollar, thus removing currency volatility altogether!

People were expecting Dubai real estate to cool off, but the current economic climate may lead it to continue for another couple of years.

While most people take investing advice from Warren Buffett... I like referring to his advice on hiring...

He says there are only three things you should look out for while hiring people -

1/ Integrity
2/ Intelligence
3/ Energy

If they don’t have the first one, the other two will kill you.

Now, most interviews test number two and three - as both intelligence and energy can be perceived and felt from the resume, and their demeanour.

It’s testing the integrity that takes the most amount of effort...

To do this, you need to ask them two questions:

1/ Tell me about a time when upholding your principles cost you something valuable... and 

2/ Describe a situation where you made a significant mistake at work. How did you handle it?

The biggest red flags in an answer would be if they blame the failure on the team and can’t take ownership... or even if they have no failure story to share, or give non specific vague answers.

Someone who gives you a weakness that is actually a strength is the biggest bullcrapper on the planet because you want someone who can be real and own up to their genuine shortcomings.

Combine the above with two solid references of people you can speak with and check the above... It could be superiors, peers, but someone of credibility who can validate it.

You could ask the references to rate the candidate’s trustworthiness on a scale of 1 to 10, and if they give him an 8 or 9, ask why they deducted a point and what would make them worthy of a full 10.

If you’re looking for another passport, Portugal offers the highest ROI for Indians compared to any other citizenship program in the world…

While the Indian passport gives you visa free access to about 60 countries, the Portugal passport gives you 188 countries visa free, including US, Canada, UK and the whole of Europe.

To be eligible, you have to visit Portugal for just 7 days per year, and maintain an investment in their country for 5 years, on which you get about 12% per annum, and I’ll explain how.

The citizenship of UK costs about Rs 21 crores (GBP 2 million), of Malta costs over Rs 6 crores (EUR 700k+), but for Portugal it costs just about Rs 3 crores (EUR 350k)

You can invest this amount in real estate in Portugal, where since 2015, properties have appreciated by 8-10% annually, while giving 4-7% rental yields, thus giving 12% annual returns.

A tech company founder from Bangalore invested about Rs 4.5 crores (EUR 500k) in a Lisbon apartment five years ago - the property appreciated by 47%, generated rental income, AND he used Portugal as his European headquarters, expanding his business across the EU.

And here’s a sweetener… Portugal follows the “Non-Habitual Resident” tax program - you pay just 20% flat tax rate on professional income and potentially zero tax on foreign-source income for 10 years.

There’s a lot more nuance to this. Do it in consultation with a professional.

What’s the Cost of Living for a Nuclear Family in Toronto? 

How much money would you need if you want to move to Toronto with your family — that is, spouse and a young child — and lead a decent life?

-	Rentals will cost you about Rs 2.5 lakhs monthly (CAD 3500 – 4000), for a 2-bedroom apartment in a decent neighborhood like North York, Etobicoke, or Mississauga.

-	Groceries would add up to another Rs 75k (CAD 1250).

-	Transportation — whether it’s public transport (TTC) or a personal car lease plus insurance — would cost another Rs 50k (CAD 750).

-	Childcare can easily cost Rs 1 lakh (CAD 1500–2000) per month, if both parents are working.

-	Eating out, entertainment and lifestyle expenses: keep aside about Rs 1 lakh (CAD 1750).

-	Insurance, contingencies, medicals (even with OHIP in place): another Rs 50k (CAD 750).

Which means at least Rs 6 lakhs (roughly CAD 10,000) per month.

If your earning in Toronto is going to be less than CAD 120,000 post tax annually, you may be better off staying in India and earning Rs 2.5 lakhs per month instead.

This means, try and get a pre-tax salary package of no less than CAD 150,000 per annum for a half decent life.

Now, people also live in Toronto for easily 30% lesser than the above figures, but that’s with really cutting corners and being harsh on your spends.

This is how I’m seeing a few people double their pay in their 30s…

It comes with some risk but the pay off is totally worth it.

The concept of a Mini Retirement is increasingly becoming popular…
 
Increasingly, a number of people in their 30s are frustrated that their jobs keep them so busy with such administrative and repetitive work that even if they want to learn new skills to stay relevant, there is absolutely no time with work meetings, travel to the office, family commitments and more…
 
And this is even more frustrating when people realize that their juniors are switching companies, taking bigger promotions, and their experience is rusting their ability to be hired elsewhere…
 
Which is why the concept of a mini retirement is picking up where people decide to take a break from work for around 12 months…
 
Which would mean building up a fund to last you a year of expenses, moving to a cheaper destination or a tier 2 city, and then spending the next six months on just learning new skills like AI, Blockchain, or in whatever domain you want to upskill in…

And then coming back to applying to newer roles in the latter half, giving yourself one year to upskill and restart your career…
 
Some people are also taking up part time freelancing gigs during this period which helps them stay in the zone of working about 10 hours a week, while keeping the remaining time free to learn.
 
Think it’s a low cost self taught MBA break because even MBA colleges are not being able to keep up with new skills in today’s time.
 
These breaks are also being called “Mini Retirements” on the resume instead of sabbaticals, which when asked about during an interview, gives you an opportunity to show how you are invested in learning even when your colleagues are just doing the old things.
 
Companies like Adobe, Linkedin and AirBnB also have extended leave programs that help retain talent and reduce burnout.
 
The stigma attached to it is definitely going away.

I want to tell you something that happened with me yesterday…

I was checking into a hotel in New York… and saw that the person checking us in at the property was of brown descent…

Generally, over a chat I appreciated his swift assistance with the process, and over the conversation asked him where he was from…

He stopped for a few seconds and said Gujarat…

I could tell from the way he spoke that he was from across the border in Pakistan… and chose to say Gujarat because its a safe word that gives the impression that one is from India while few people know that there is a city called Gujarat in Pakistan.

And I’ve seen this time and again not just in the US, but in Canada, UK, Europe… no matter where you go…

People from Pakistan seem so embarrassed of their country often times that they present themselves as Indians…

You’ll see this also in the fact that most of the Indian restaurants being run in the UK are being run by Pakistanis but they will call it an Indian Restaurant and not Pakistani.

So it’s not something they’ll say to people who are Indian…

It’s often clear that a lot of Pakistanis abroad in Western economies are embarrassed of not just how their government behaves but also how it is perceived globally.

I have absolutely no hate for civilians and wish the well to all, but I also want to take this as an opportunity to say that the Indian brand has helped a lot of people across the border actually find a livelihood in other countries, and they should be mindful of how they behave with our country.

My condolences to everyone from India who lost their lives in the war, and a reminder to the world…

That its always Jai Hind before anything else.

After Analogue Paneer… the next product you’ll see a lot of adulteration and fakes are in your coffee…

In the past 5 years, coffee prices have gone up from $1000 a tonne to $5000 a tonne.

It’s a 5X increase in 5 years, and a 3X in the past 3 years…

It’s all because the demand for coffee around the world has gone so up north, that people who never cared about it earlier are now into collecting coffees, and enjoying unique brews multiple times a day…

This is fuelled with constantly dropping yields…

Two if the largest suppliers in the world are Brazil and Vietnam, and they’re both seeing a poor crop season.

There is a high chance that these prices may remain unpredictable for another couple of years… so coffee companies in India and around the world are facing a very tough time with increasing costs, and pressure to increase price which they feel the market will not accept…

I predict that your Instant Coffee brands will soon change their composition to add a lot more chicory powder, which is the root of a plant, roasted and mixed into coffee blends…

As for the cafés you go to, if they are really into serving the best single origin coffees, their prices should go up by about 20%… so a Rs 300 cup may now cost closer to Rs 400

Also, currently, the instant coffee brands have 70% actual coffee and the balance is chicory, so remember to check the ingredients to see what you’re really drinking.

Known for its soothing properties, peppermint can help you find relief from common IBS symptoms. By blocking calcium channels and relaxing muscles in the gastrointestinal tract, it eases cramping and discomfort.

While peppermint tea offers some benefits, enteric-coated peppermint oil formulations are favored because they are more likely to release directly in the small intestine, providing more effective relief from IBS symptoms. 

Some studies suggest peppermint has antibacterial properties that may reduce SIBO bacteria, too!  Peppermint influences serotonin receptors in your gut, which play a crucial role in regulating bowel movements. By affecting these receptors, peppermint may help bring more balance to your digestive system.

Please note: If you suffer from heartburn or acid reflux, peppermint may worsen your symptoms as it can relax the sphincter between the stomach and esophagus, allowing stomach acids to flow back into the esophagus.

Talk to your provider about incorporating peppermint into your routine for a calmer, happier gut! 💜

Information from: The Microbiome Connection

Happy @WorldMicrobiomeDay! 🌎🦠 This year's theme is diet.

Here are three diets often used to manage SIBO and IBS symptoms:

1. The Elemental Diet:  A restrictive diet that replaces food and drinks with liquid or powder formulas that are easy to digest and provide a complete nutritional profile. The formulas break down proteins, fats, and carbohydrates into their basic building blocks, such as amino acids, fatty acids, and sugars, and combine them with vitamins, minerals, and electrolytes. Check out @elementaldiet

2. The Low Fermentation Diet: A restrictive diet that aims to help people with small intestinal bacterial overgrowth or irritable bowel syndrome. The diet limits fermentable carbohydrates that can feed bacteria. It also includes meal timing guidelines to allow the gut to empty out between meals. Check out @goodlfeofficial @mastprogram 

3. The Low FODMAP Diet: A restrictive diet that limits foods that contain fermentable oligosaccharides, disaccharides, monosaccharides, and polyols (FODMAPs). FODMAPs are short-chain carbohydrates that are poorly absorbed by the small intestine and ferment in the colon. Check out @monashfodmap

Remember, always consult your doctor before trying a new diet. Here's to a healthy microbiome!

Normally, the small intestine contains relatively few bacteria compared to the large intestine or colon. However, with SIBO, bacteria from the colon migrate and take up residence in the small intestine, leading to an overgrowth. 🧫🔬

This overpopulation of bacteria starts feasting on your dietary nutrients before your body can fully digest and absorb them. As the bacteria consume the food passing through, they produce excess gases as a byproduct. It's this gaseous overproduction that leads to the hallmark SIBO symptoms like bloating, abdominal pain, diarrhea, and flatulence. 💨🙁

When bacteria exist in their proper territories and quantities, digestion hums along undisturbed. But when their balance gets disrupted through migration and overgrowth, SIBO's unpleasant digestive woes can take over your daily life.

Learn more on the Trio-Smart Website! 💜

Neglect something long enough, and don’t be surprised when it’s not the same anymore. Pay attention to what matters before it’s too late.

It's easy to assume that cutting ties with the people you thought would be in your life forever is easy but in reality, its usually attached with grief, a deep ache of knowing you had to choose yourself at the expense of what was familiar. 

Healing sometimes requires us to release, so we can let go off the connections that are weighing us down. 

And the hardest part is standing firm in that decision when nostalgia tries to pull you back. 

But here’s the truth: your well-being is worth more than any history shared. 

You are allowed to outgrow spaces, even when it hurts.

Affirmation: I release what no longer serves my peace 🌻

Drop a ❤ if this resonates

You deserve softness. You deserve love that feels safe, joy that feels effortless, and a life that doesn’t ask you to constantly prove your worth. You don’t have to earn rest. You don’t have to chase peace. You are already enough, exactly as you are. Breathe easy. Love easy. You deserve it all.

Hoping this reaches the right people today 🤍

Today marks the 158th anniversary of Juneteenth. 
 
As the longest-standing national celebration of the end of slavery in the United States, this day serves as a significant reminder of slavery’s enduring impact. While commemorating the end of slavery, we acknowledge and reflect on the injustices and challenges Black Americans still endure.
 
We are proud to observe this day company-wide across connectRN. Our commitment to the nursing community—and one another—is to create a safe and supportive environment.
 
Today, we stand with our community, and encourage all Connectors to reflect on and commemorate this day.

Nurses need flexibility. They need it to pursue the passions they have in life beyond nursing and to honor who they are. @catalystforselfcare says that nurses taking on non-traditional roles is not only about burnout prevention but also signifies growth in the healthcare community. We agree.

Explore this idea and other fascinating results from our survey as we try to define the “New Nurse.” Link in bio.

#ListenToNurses #TheNewNurse #NursesOfInstagram #RNs #LPNs #NurseLife

We surveyed 1,300+ nurses to understand what they want, where they want to go, and what it will take to get there.

Nurses are seeking a different path for themselves. They love being a nurse and are committed to caring for others. But they also want to be “more than a nurse.”

What does that look like? 50% of nurses have a side hustle. 34% of which are in pursuit of new skills and/or are following a passion. 

Nurses need flexibility, not constraints to create the life they want. The evolution of nursing is here.

“I create my own life by dreaming, making goals and being persistent.” 

Watch this space for more insight into The New Nurse. In collaboration with @thenursingbeat. 

#thenewnurse #listentonurses #nursesidehustle #nursingstudent #nursingschool #registerednurse #nursesofinstagram #nurselife

As Pride month comes to a close – our education should never stop. 

As much as Pride is a celebration, it’s also a time for learning and education 📖

People’s health needs change as they grow older, but for members of the aging LGBTQ+ community, those shifting needs are often different from the needs of the general population.

Whether it’s coping with the long-term effects of discrimination, or combatting the higher risks of social isolation, it’s essential to know what LGBTQ+ resources exist for older people, and how to help them find the support they deserve.

Click the link in our bio for additional resources that can help you learn more about aging LGBTQ+ adults’ healthcare rights, the type of healthcare they might need, and the ways they can find support and services for their overall wellbeing.

June is National Pride Month, a time to honor the impact LGBTQ+ people have had on the world, and especially in nursing.

It’s natural to think that treating all patients with the same respect will minimize the discrimination LGBTQ+ people face in healthcare settings, but that’s not always the case. 

LGBTQ+ people still face many barriers to receiving the optimal healthcare they deserve.

Here are 5 specific strategies for how you can help improve this community’s quality of care.

This year, we’re doing Nurses Week differently. 

We are shining a light on a side of nursing that's often overlooked: how physically demanding it is to do your job.

Lifting a patient twice your size? No problem.

Walking 16,000 steps over 12 hours, with a 30 minute break? You got this.

Juggling linens, equipment, and emotions? Yes, yes, and yes.

You are the unseen athletes of healthcare. 

The physical endurance and mental toughness to do what you do, every day, should be celebrated!

Follow along this Nurses Week for some fun surprises we have planned for you.

Notice The Nurses: CLARA BARTON

Closing out our series this month is Clara Barton, whose nursing career started on the battlefields of the Civil War. 

She didn’t discriminate with her aid, providing care and supplies to soldiers from both sides, as well as reading to them and helping them write letters home. 

Wanting to do more after the war ended, she brought the Red Cross movement to America and served as its president for 23 years, bringing care across the nation and the world. 

#NoticeTheNurses #WomensHistoryMonth

Notice The Nurses: LILLIAN D. WALD

Lillian D. Wald was the pioneering force behind the practice of community nursing. 

After working with struggling families in New York’s Lower East Side, she started the Visiting Nursing Service of New York to bring affordable healthcare to the neighborhood. 

From there, she dedicated her life to activism, campaigning for women’s suffrage, and supporting racial integration. 

She also co-founded the Henry Street Settlement, a non-profit organization that continues to provide social services, arts programs, and healthcare to New Yorkers of all ages to this day. 

#NoticeTheNurses #WomensHistoryMonth

Should you work as a 1099 or W2 employee?
 
Nurses, SAVE this post if you’re considering your options.

And make sure you know the benefits of W2 and the risks of 1099 contracting!
 
Benefits of W2 employment:
 
1️⃣. Benefits (if you elect to have them and meet hourly requirements)
2️⃣. Workers comp (if you get hurt on the job)
3️⃣. Unemployment insurance
4️⃣. Overtime (1099 contractors are straight pay, no matter how many hours they work)
5️⃣. No required quarterly tax payments (pay at the end of the year)

Notice The Nurses: DR. BETTY FERRELL

Dr. Betty Ferrell, Ph.D., M.S.N., CHPN, is a highly regarded, published, and awarded nurse, whose lifelong work is dedicated to making hospice and palliative care an essential part of healthcare.

When she began working as a nurse over 45 years ago, there were fewer than ten hospices in the US and palliative care was not widely known. But with the help of her efforts and numerous projects (including the End-of-Life Nursing Education Consortium that she founded and led), palliative care has grown to be a global practice. 

She currently serves as the Director of Nursing Research and Education and a professor at City of Hope in Southern California.

#NoticeTheNurses #WomensHistoryMonth

Notice The Nurses: VIRGINIA HENDERSON

Virginia Henderson was a huge influence in nursing education and practice. 

After getting her start in public nursing, she became the first full-time nursing instructor in Virginia and pushed for the inclusion of psychiatric nursing in the state’s healthcare curriculum. 

She went on to develop the Need Theory, a checklist for patient care that prioritizes their ability to be independent and care for themselves after being released from the hospital. 

This theory helped to define the role of a nurse and still remains in use today.

#NoticeTheNurses #WomensHistoryMonth

Notice The Nurses: SUSIE KING TAYLOR

Capping off our series this month is Susie King Taylor. 

This trailblazer is known for being the first Black nurse during the Civil War, volunteering for the Union Army to care for sick and injured soldiers. 

She often risked her own health and safety by sneaking into the tents of those who had been quarantined with smallpox and providing them with the care they needed. 

Her legacy is one of unbounded kindness and a dedication to compassionate care. 

#NoticeTheNurses #BlackHistoryMonth

Notice The Nurses: HAZEL JOHNSON-BROWN

After being denied entry to nursing schools in her hometown because she was Black, Hazel Johnson-Brown moved to New York City and graduated from the Harlem School of Nursing. 

A few years after working in the Harlem Hospital emergency ward, she joined the US Army and helped train nurses heading to the frontlines of the Vietnam War. 

From there, she became the first Black female general and the first Black chief of the Army Nurse Corps, and eventually went on to earn a PhD in Nursing Education and Administration. 

#NoticeTheNurses #BlackHistoryMonth

Notice The Nurses: SOJOURNER TRUTH

Another name you might find familiar is that of Sojourner Truth, who was also a well-known abolitionist that escaped slavery and helped champion emancipation leading up to the Civil War.

She served as a nurse, enslaved and as a free woman, at which point she worked for the National Freedman’s Relief Association in Washington, D.C. 

While in this role, she often spoke before Congress and advocated for nursing education and formal training programs.

#NoticeTheNurses #BlackHistoryMonth

Notice The Nurses: HARRIET TUBMAN

You may know her as the famous abolitionist who helped free hundreds of enslaved people through the Underground Railroad.

But Harriet Tubman also served as a nurse during the Civil War, treating soldiers suffering from dysentery and smallpox with natural herbal remedies. 

After the war, she continued to care for others and helped establish a home for elderly African Americans.

#NoticeTheNurses #BlackHistoryMonth

Notice The Nurses: ERNEST GRANT

Continuing our series of notable nurses is Ernest Grant, the first Black male to graduate with a PhD in Nursing from UNC Greensboro. 

Driven by a lifelong passion for fire safety and prevention, he volunteered at New York Presbyterian Hospital’s Burn Center following the attacks on the World Trade Center on September 11th, helping to care for those who were injured. 

In 2018, he became the first Black male to serve as president of the American Nurses Association.

#NoticeTheNurses #BlackHistoryMonth

Notice The Nurses: EDDIE BERNICE JOHNSON

This month, we’re spotlighting the incredible contributions of Black nurses throughout history. 

First up is Eddie Bernice Johnson, who holds a host of firsts herself. 

After becoming the first Black person to serve as Chief Psychiatric Nurse at the Dallas Veterans Administration Hospital, she found a passion for activism and became the first Black woman elected to public office in Dallas. 

She went on to serve as regional director of the Department of Health, Education, and Welfare—the first woman and first Black person to hold this title—and in 1992, she became the first registered nurse elected to Congress.

#NoticeTheNurses #BlackHistoryMonth

Microlearning is like having a handy knowledge snack pack. Short videos, infographics, or quick quizzes deliver bite-sized lessons you can conquer in minutes. This makes them perfect for boosting information retention, applying knowledge on-the-go, and filling small skill gaps. Macrolearning, on the other hand, lets you deep dive into a subject. Think comprehensive courses or workshops with structured learning, assignments, and assessments. This is ideal for developing complex skills, building a strong knowledge foundation, and even earning certifications. 

The real magic happens when you combine these approaches. They work together to make learning efficient, engaging, and impactful. So, next time you're ready to expand your knowledge, choose the approach that fits your needs, or even use both for a well-rounded learning experience!

While it's true that the left hemisphere often handles functions like language and logic, and the right hemisphere excels in creativity and spatial reasoning, it's not a clear-cut split. In reality, both sides of your brain work together in most tasks.

Take a writing course to tap into your creativity, or try a logic puzzle to sharpen your analytical skills. The more you exercise different brain functions, the stronger and more versatile your mind becomes.

🧼✨ Your gut is like a dishwasher—and if it doesn’t clean properly, leftover food (aka bacteria) builds up in all the wrong places!  Your Migrating Motor Complex (MMC) is your gut’s built-in cleaning cycle. Every 90-120 minutes between meals, it sweeps out undigested food and bacteria with cleaning waves to keep your small intestine fresh. But if your MMC isn’t working properly (due to stress, infections, or slow motility), bacteria can stick around and overgrow—leading to SIBO or Small Intestinal Bacterial Overgrowth.

If you’re dealing with bloating, diarrhea, constipation, or feeling “backed up” after eating, your gut’s "dishwasher" might not be working properly. 🌀🚫 

✅ The Trio-Smart at-home breath test is the only test that can check for all 3 gases associated with bacterial overgrowth: Hydrogen, Methane, and Hydrogen Sulfide.

☹️ The BAD News: 1 in 9 people develop post-infectious IBS after food poisoning.
🤩 The GOOD News: You can test for it, and manage it with antibiotics!

Check out what Dr. Pimentel had to say about Post-Infectious IBS in a recent webinar:
"This type of IBS is caused by a toxin called CDTB. When exposed to CDTB, your body forms antibodies against a protein called vinculin. Vinculin is crucial for the nerves in your gut, acting like the wires to a light switch. Without proper connections, your gut doesn't function smoothly. And I've already told you, if the gut doesn't flow correctly, you get a buildup of bacteria, leading to bacterial overgrowth and IBS. That's why IBS responds to antibiotics."

Got chronic diarrhea? It could be Intestinal Sulfide Overproduction (ISO). High levels of hydrogen sulfide in your small bowel can lead to chronic, severe diarrhea. To find out if you have ISO, you must use a breath test...
BUT conventional breath tests only measure 2 gases: Hydrogen (SIBO) and Methane (IMO)

Trio-Smart tests for all 3 gases: Hydrogen, Methane, and Hydrogen Sulfide. This gives you a complete picture of your gut health. If you test positive for ISO, your provider can help you manage your symptoms with a personalized treatment plan.

Want to learn more? Follow us @gemellibiotech and check out triosmartbreath.com.

On this day 57 years ago, Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. delivered his final, prophetic speech: 'I've Been to the Mountaintop.' ✊🏾🔥"⁠
⁠
Standing before a crowd in Memphis on April 3, 1968, Dr. King spoke with an urgency that still resonates today. He reflected on the struggles of the Civil Rights Movement, the fight for economic justice, and the promise of a better future. His words on economic power and collective action still resonate today.⁠
⁠
💬 “We've got to strengthen Black institutions. I call upon you to take your money out of the banks downtown and deposit your money in Tri-State Bank—we want a ‘bank-in’ movement in Memphis.”⁠
⁠
Dr. King understood that economic empowerment was key to liberation. He urged Black communities to invest in their own financial institutions, boycott businesses that exploited Black workers, and build collective economic strength. His message is a reminder that where we spend and invest our money is a powerful tool for change.⁠
⁠
Less than 24 hours later, he was assassinated, but his words and mission live on. Dr. King's vision for justice, equality, and economic empowerment remains as powerful and necessary as ever. #BlackExcellence

On this day 61 years ago, Malcolm X delivered his iconic 'Ballot or the Bullet' speech in Cleveland, Ohio, on April 3, 1964. 🔥 His message was clear: Black Americans must use their political power strategically and demand their civil rights.⁠
⁠
🗳️ 'The time has come for Black people to fight back in self-defense whenever and wherever they are unjustly and unlawfully attacked.'⁠
⁠
💡 He challenged systemic oppression and called for unity beyond religious or ideological differences, stating:⁠
"Whether you are a Christian or a Muslim or a nationalist, we all have the same problem. They don’t hang you because you're a Baptist; they hang you because you’re Black!"⁠
⁠
📢 Malcolm X urged the Black community to use the ballot wisely. Demand real change from politicians or refuse to support those who don’t serve Black interests. His message remains as relevant today as it was in 1964.⁠
⁠
✊🏾 Do you think his words still apply today? Drop your thoughts in the comments! 👇🏾⁠
⁠
#BlackHistory #MalcolmX #BallotOrTheBullet #CivilRights #BlackEmpowerment #BlackExcellence

41 years ago today, Coach John Thompson 🕊️ became the FIRST Black head coach to win an NCAA basketball championship! Leading Georgetown University to victory in 1984, Thompson not only secured a historic title but also paved the way for future Black coaches in college basketball.⁠
⁠
Born and raised in Washington, D.C., Thompson was a dominant force on the court before stepping into coaching. A 6’10” center, he played college ball at Providence College, where he led the team to the NIT Championship in 1963 and became an All-American. After a brief stint in the NBA with the Boston Celtics—winning two championships as a backup to Bill Russell—he transitioned to coaching, taking over Georgetown’s basketball program in 1972.⁠
⁠
Thompson transformed the Hoyas into a powerhouse, mentoring future NBA legends like Patrick Ewing, Alonzo Mourning, and Allen Iverson. Off the court, he was a fierce advocate for Black student-athletes, famously walking out on an NCAA meeting in protest of rules that he felt unfairly targeted underprivileged players. 👏🏾 #BlackExcellence #BlackHistory⁠
⁠
May he continue to rest in power. 🕊️

On this day in 1965, the historic Selma to Montgomery March culminated as thousands of demonstrators arrived at the Alabama State Capitol, marking a pivotal moment in the fight for voting rights. ⁠
⁠
Led by Dr. Martin Luther King Jr., the marchers embarked on a five-day, 54-mile journey. Under federal protection, they covered about 12 miles a day and slept in fields and makeshift camps along U.S. Route 80, enduring physical exhaustion and threats to demand equal voting rights for African Americans.⁠
⁠
The march followed earlier attempts that were met with violent opposition, notably the events of "Bloody Sunday" on March 7, 1965, when peaceful protesters were brutally attacked at the Edmund Pettus Bridge. Despite these challenges, the marchers persevered, and their efforts contributed significantly to the passage of the Voting Rights Act of 1965, a landmark achievement in the Civil Rights Movement. ✊🏾 #BlackHistory⁠
⁠

I’m all in on making real estate listings more transparent. Every buyer should be able to see every home for sale—no hidden inventory, no insider access required. 

When listings are open, buyers win with better choices, sellers win with fair competition, and prices stay honest. This move pushes the industry forward and opens the door wider for more people to become homeowners. I’m watching to see which brokerage steps up next. 

Sellers deserve the full truth—not advice that keeping a home off-market will get them more money, when the data says otherwise. Transparency isn’t about forcing anyone’s hand. It’s about making sure buyers and sellers have real choices and fewer regrets.

"Together, we can help the rest of the world create cannabis in a very controlled environment, successfully."

In this episode of Grower Stories, we’re heading to Cuba, Missouri, to visit Robust Cannabis, a cultivation facility that’s taking year-round growing to the next level. 🌱❄️☀️

"BioTherm is the premium product for HVAC in cannabis."

Discover how their BioTherm PlantCentric™ climate system helps them maintain consistent, high-quality growth, no matter what the unpredictable Missouri weather throws their way. From precise root zone heating to tailored environmental control, Robust Cannabis proves that smart technology and great growers are the perfect combination for success. 

Shoutout to @robust_cannabis, @thebradrhodes, @tylerhannegan, and @dragon_growz_mo for trusting BioTherm to support your vision. It’s an honor to provide the climate systems that help you grow exceptional cannabis in a precisely controlled environment. Proud to be part of your journey!

Seeing double? You’re right. Two irrigation pre-heating skids headed to one facility, helping deliver consistently tempered water, boosting nutrient uptake, protecting roots, and supporting stronger crops year-round. 💦🔥

Big day for big heat! 🚛🔥⁠
⁠
Our latest DuoFin system is loaded up and on its way to a customer, bringing precision root zone heating to 48,000 square feet of growing space.⁠
⁠
DuoFin delivers consistent, efficient warmth right where plants need it most — at the roots — helping growers maximize crop quality, accelerate growth, and reduce energy costs.⁠
⁠
Another project powered by smart heating and strong results. 🌱
If you see us parked out front, something good is growing inside. 🔥
We can’t wait to see you at @greentechrai!

We’re excited to announce that BioTherm will be exhibiting at GreenTech Amsterdam this June! With over 45 years of experience, we’re proud to lead the way in greenhouse climate technology—empowering growers to create ideal environments for healthy, high-yield crops.⁠
⁠
We'll be showcasing our Advanced Hydronic Heating Systems—energy-efficient, low-temp solutions that integrate with alternative energy sources like heat pumps, solar, and waste heat.⁠
⁠
If you’re attending, come find us and see how we’re helping growers optimize root zone temperatures, lower energy costs, and grow smarter—year-round.

Grower Stories, Episode 21

In this episode of our Grower Stories series, we head to Missouri for an inside look at Delphi Management, a 10,000 sq. ft. hybrid, positive-pressure greenhouse facility. Join us as we talk with David Risley, Director of Cultivation, about how they're pushing the limits of year-round growing—even in Missouri's unpredictable climate.

Delphi retrofitted their facility to combat extreme weather conditions with a BioTherm Plantcentric® System, a cutting-edge climate solution that helps maintain consistent growing temperatures, no matter what’s happening outside. They’ve also implemented a dissolved oxygen system to boost root health and improve plant performance.

With BioTherm technologies in place, Delphi Management is equipped to grow high-quality crops year-round—efficiently and reliably.
Still kickin’ since 1981 — this header’s been keeping the bench heat flowing for over 40 years. Talk about old-school reliability.

BioTherm makes hot water heating easy! ⁠
⁠
This shows our team manufacturing 2 different boiler room systems, one is using copper, the other traditional welded steel tubing. The copper "boiler loop" is going to integrate 3 boilers together (2 now, 1 future), and the steel one will connect 4- 400,000 BTUH high-efficiency boilers. The copper system is bound for North Carolina, and the Steel system is going to Florida— both are going to blueberry growers! 
⁠
By doing the hard parts of BioTherm systems with pre-assembly, we make it easy for growers to benefit from world-class, high-efficiency heating.

Having your bank accounts in your name alone puts your family at risk.

When you pass away, they’ll have to go through a lengthy probate process, which prevents them from taking action.

That’s why I recommend putting your bank accounts in a revocable living trust so your family can avoid the lengthy probate process.

If you live in a blended family, pay attention to this.

You don’t want to end up in a situation where the step-siblings inherit someone’s childhood home, one that they didn’t even live in.

Sadly this does happen, and having a revocable living trust helps protect against it.

👇How to protect your kids’ inheritance:

(save this)

1: Create a revocable trust for yourself.

Then, instead of leaving them a lump sum in your trust….

Add provisions that will create a trust for your kids when you die.

Within that trust, you control when and how they get the money, even after you’re gone.

2: Set conditions.

You can distribute funds for specific milestones like:

- college

- buying a house

- starting a business

3: Protect from creditors & divorce.

With a trust, the money stays protected from

- lawsuits

- bankruptcy

- a bad divorce

The goal?

Protect your kids and the legacy you worked so hard to build.

And if you happen to think a man who took entire days of his life recording himself.

Doing what?

Reading comic books like they were bedtime stories. Doing multiple voices and sound effects and then taking stills from iconic pages and creating a very crude but effective animatic (minimalistic animation, motion of whole foreground Images)
He would do breakdowns of entire story archive etc. And on occasion would even give small compare and contrast sessions of books vs a recent mcu or dceu movie.

He Unfortunately passed away this year due to an auto accident and I, among others, know how much power an entire industry is, for losing him.

If you are In a catagory against him on the ballot in 2024, i am unsure how you would feel okay if even by accident  you managed to take any kind of honor from someone who literally never asked  for someone to honor him just the ones he loved. 
I cannot tell you what to do if you are someone the cbca put on the ballot against him. But if it's me or any one that would be in My general orbit. Anything other than taking a knee is both pretentious and truly Tone deaf In my opinion.

🎼 "Deadly Routine"

"Overtime", the latest release born from the collaboration of two friends and seasoned artists—"Illogick" and "Grim Logick"—delivers what I consider a true trap hip-hop experience. This track speaks from a place of deep inner pain, connecting directly with its audience.
The two verses felt like a journey—one where I traveled alongside the artists. Their impressive flow switches, combined with sharp and emotionally resonant lyrics, created a powerful experience that reminded me what real trap music can sound like.
On the instrumental side, the production was built on a minimal yet incredibly catchy melodic structure. I have to say, no one but "H-L Beatz" could have created such a dark, creepy atmosphere with this level of finesse. The eerie, almost nightmarish sound elements perfectly complement the lyrical content, never allowing the listener to feel at ease. Meanwhile, the bass and drums hit hard, following an unconventional rhythmic pattern that adds even more punch to the track.
If you're like me and constantly on the lookout for something different in trap music, this is one track you absolutely shouldn’t miss.

Humans of HOKA: Tara Warren (@runwithtara) 

Last summer, Tara Warren completed the Rocky Mountain Slam, a challenge that includes racing four of the toughest 100-mile trail races in four months: Bighorn, Hardrock, Wasatch and Bear. When Tara crossed the final finish line at the Bear 100 in Logan, Utah, she became the eighth woman to ever do so, and the first woman to accomplish the feat since 2016 - the same year her mother died of ALS. For Tara, completing the Slam also meant honoring her mother by fundraising for the ALS Association. 

In our latest #HumansofHOKA film, Tara shares her running journey, the process of completing the Slam and how her mother continues to inspire her every step of the way.

This year, in partnership with @HOKA and with support from seven of our locations, we focused our Earth Day efforts on direct, actionable community impact. Over 120 internal volunteers identified and addressed local environmental opportunities.

In Miami, our South Beach and MDD teams partnered with VolunteerCleanup.org for a beach cleanup at South Pointe Park, supporting their mission to reduce marine debris and single-use plastics.

In Hawaii, we joined Kākoʻo ʻŌiwi to plant 1,100 taro in a new Lo‘i on land that hadn’t been farmed in nearly 80 years, helping perpetuate Native Hawaiian farming practices.

In California, our West Hollywood, Beverly Hills, and Malibu teams worked with Surfrider LA to clean Zuma Beach, collecting 15+ pounds of trash and supporting ocean protection and plastic reduction.

All New York locations came together with Harlem Grown for the second year, filling over 15 garden beds at their new 139th St. site, supporting local food access and youth education.

In Paris, our team toured the Syctom Sorting Center, learning about their ability to process up to 10 tons of packaging waste per hour and the importance of recycling.

In Toronto, we partnered with LiveGreenTO for a cleanup at Trinity Bellwoods Park and took part in recycling education, supporting climate action and greener living.

In Tokyo, our team joined Urban Farmland and Disaster Prevention Garden at Harajuku Harappa Farm to learn composting, dig soil, and plant in soil made from recycled materials including Kith Treats Tokyo coffee grounds.

On this Global Earth Day, we continue to encourage local action in the fight for a more sustainable future. Thank you to HOKA for empowering this initiative.

Some say running in the mountains is a bit crazy. Maybe they’re right. But it’s the kind of madness that makes me feel the most alive.

I’m incredibly grateful and proud to announce that I’ll be partnering with @hoka for the next three years! 

For me, running has always been a way to understand more about myself and the world. As a pro athlete, it’s definitely much about running fast and performance, but the real competition is primarily within myself. Running has taught me to embrace change, to keep moving forward and to seek growth in every step.

What feels really special about joining the Hoka family is that they empower me to feel my authentic self, to embrace both my triumphs and my vulnerabilities, and to share the self-doubt and uncertainty that all of us face. We are all human, we all face the same uncertainties, no matter our achievements or personal stories. I want to send the message that runners of all abilities can relate to the highs, the lows, and everything in between that I experience. I’m also very excited to contribute to the growth of the sport that I love, with a brand that is also making a profound impact on trail running and the trail community at large.

Thank you for being part of this journey with me, it means the world. Here’s to more trails, more adventures, and a little more madness ☺️

@hoka @hoka_eu

I'm not a stranger to running, but I do encounter moments when I feel overwhelmed by the sense of failure. Remaining consistent with a healthy challenge and checking in with my online community helps me see my goals through. Last year, I felt this way after returning to running after having surgery in the middle of my marathon training season. I wasn't certain how my body would respond to exercise post-hysterectomy. Instead of trying to hammer through all of the miles that I missed while recovering, I adjusted my schedule accordingly. I prioritized moving slowly, steadily, and safely to reach finish lines. After finishing my fall race calendar, I promised myself that I'd dedicate these winter months to building up my foundation and moving like a well-oiled machine. Allow my experience to serve as a testament to stray away from the laundry list of what ifs, listen to your body, remain consistent, and focus on the miles in front of you.

Sometimes we return to the things we love to remind us of who we are. 💙

This past year brought some of the biggest changes of my life — a diagnosis of ADHD, depression, and C-PTSD, along with navigating a lot of new and more intensive ways of coping and healing. I carried a weight in my chest, a numbness I couldn’t quite describe, and an overwhelm of uncertainty – I knew, for the sake of my overall health, that I needed movement back in my life. 

I wanted a goal that was big, uncomfortable, and meaningful. A challenge to hold me accountable and reconnect me with running and myself. The NYC Marathon became that goal, @brasforgirlsorg became the “why”, and running once again became my safe place to land.

Thank you, @hoka, for giving me the platform to share my story and for the support every step (literally!) of the way. 💙 Link in bio to read the full blog!

Welcome to the HOKA Team, @colinsahlman! 😎

Heading into the 800-meter race at the Desert Heat Classic in April, Colin Sahlman didn’t know what to expect. The 1500-meter runner from Northern Arizona University was about to race Rivaldo Marshall of Iowa, the reigning NCAA indoor champion, in his first 800 of the season. 

Though it was a daunting match-up, some sage advice helped Colin shift his mindset. For the last two years, Colin’s coach Mike Smith has reminded him to focus on competing against other runners, instead of going for a time on the track. In every race, the All-American practices ways to beat as many competitors as he can while trying not to focus on the clock. “[Mike] helped me recognize that racing is more important than running fast, but if you race to win, fast times will eventually come with that,” Colin says. 

The strategy paid off in Tucson, Arizona. For two laps, Colin put himself in a position to win, and ultimately sprinted through the finish line in a 1:45.63 personal best, beating Rivaldo by almost a full second. The victory also set the tone for a breakthrough track season. 🚀

Colin went on to finish fourth in the 1500 at the NCAA championships and compete through the semifinal at the U.S. Olympic Trials as one of the only collegians in a field of professionals. Looking back, Colin attributes a lot of his success to trusting his ability as a runner, something he hopes more athletes embrace as an important skill. 

“View each competition as practice to learn from your competitors and from your own mistakes,” he says. “The more you practice the better decision you can make in competition later.” 

This fall, Colin is leading NAU into an exciting cross-country season in which the Lumberjacks return as the No. 4-ranked team in the country. On the track, Colin is aiming to win his first NCAA title and compete for a spot on Team USA headed to the 2025 world championships in Tokyo. 🙌

Join us in welcoming @colinsahlman as he competes for more big wins this season! 

📸 @nickisabella.photography 

#FlyHumanFly #HOKA #TeamHOKA

Welcome to the HOKA Team, @maggi.congdon!

Maggi Congdon is not afraid to take risks when it comes to racing. And that courage has paid off with a rise she never imagined. 🏔️

This year, the senior at Northern Arizona University (NAU) lowered her 1500-meter personal best from 4:16 to 4:02 with an incredible leap at the U.S. Olympic Track and Field Trials. On the national stage, Maggi cut almost eight seconds off her previous career best to make the women’s 1500m final. On June 30, she was the only collegian stepping up against the best professional middle-distance runners in the country. 

So, how did the runner from Steamboat Springs, Colorado, who came to NAU with a 4:59 1600-meter PR, make the jump? It all comes down to consistency in training and recovery, she says. 

“My biggest piece of advice for anyone else who is aiming for a breakthrough is just to stick with it through both the good patches and the rough patches and know that if you put 100% in, it may take time, but you will eventually see those results follow,” Maggi says.

Now as part of the HOKA Team, Maggi is leading NAU to an NCAA title chase in cross country. Last year, the women’s team finished second at the NCAA championships. This fall, they’re aiming to top the podium and dethrone three-time champions North Carolina State. 

Follow @maggi.congdon’s journey as she chases more breakthroughs on the grass and beyond this year! 💥

📸 @clippedinmedia

Traveling and hiking are 2 of my favorite activities and when I can combine them, it’s a great day! #ad

While visiting Hawaii again for work, I got away from the hustle and bustle of Waikiki to test out the new Speedgoat 6 on a trail I’ve never done before. I love that these shoes can double as a travel shoe as well as one I know I can trust hiking in the rainforest (or anywhere)! 

About 1.5miles into this hike, the clouds rolled in and graced the day with a downpour. It’s not the first time I’ve been testing out a HOKA shoe on a trail and rain made an appearance! But how often can you hike through the rainforest while it’s actually raining? It was stunning, refreshing, and smelled amazing. I had no worries about comfort, traction or support because the Speedgoat 6 made sure every step was steady, supported and cushioned. I really put these shoes through their paces. 

I finished 5 miles of hiking, climbed over 1100ft of elevation in both rain and sun, and over varied terrain including wet roots, mud, rocks, dirt, thorny bushes, and leaves. I also found a beautiful flower that represented all the colors on my shoes. Nature IS the inspiration! The Speedgoat 6 really is the GOAT for trail runners and hikers!

To learn more about the Speedgoat 6, visit the @hoka website (link in bio)!

As the 2024 holiday season quickly approaches, our family and businesses are proud to be a small part of bringing cheer and joy to the children and teens at @childrensharborinc. ♥️🎄🎁

For over 27 years, Children’s Harbor has been providing a harbor of hope and healing right here in our South Florida community for children who have been impacted by the trauma of child abuse.

Children’s Harbor’s mission is powerful:

We Keep Kids Safe.
Our main campus provides a family environment to teenagers in foster care and their younger siblings.

We Help Families Heal.
Our Family Strengthening team prevents kids from coming into foster care by providing in-house counseling and support to families who are struggling in our community.

We Shine a Light Toward Hope.
Our independent living programs provide support and wrap-around guidance to teens who have aged out of the foster care system through the early stages of adulthood.

If this message touches your heart this holiday season and you feel moved to give, please visit the link in my bio and give the gift of holiday cheer. It can be a small gift (or a large one 😊). No matter what it will impact the lives of this kids in ways many of us cannot even imagine.

🔑3 Algorithm Keys for BIG Reach👇

These Algorithm updates come directly from the head of Instagram, Adam Mosseri.

Adam said that IG is now trying to “…give every piece of content on Instagram, a chance to be recommended to people who don’t follow you”.

The crazy thing is this isn’t even *new news, but it’s a game-changer for reach & most people are still not taking advantage of it.

So what should you do to make sure you keep getting pushed in the algorithm & reach more new potential followers?

3 Ways to Leverage the Algorithm:

1. Bite-size value content

Focus on reels that give a lot of value, in a short amount of time.

One of the best ways to stand out to stranger, is to offer clear value, & make a strong impression in a short amount of time.
Don’t waste people’s time. Keep things short & sweet.

Yes, I mean including short reels (5-15 sec.) as a major part of your outreach strategy.

People LOVE to save & share: lists, quotes, how-tos, & step-by-step instructions

2. UP-Level your Hook Game

If you don’t have a strong hook game, people will scroll past your reels.

So your no.1 priority should be supercharging your hooks with:

Curiosity, interesting visuals, speaking to a very specific person, problem, result or situation & using numbers.
(You can look at how my hook used these)

👉Or Comment “57” to get my free Viral Hooks Cheat Sheet

3. Outreach content strategy: Instead of hoping your ideal followers will discover you, make it easy for them.

What are the top questions they’re asking? What are they searching for on Insta and in google?

Who are the trending people & what are the trending topics related to your niche that you can talk about to get in front of your ideal audience?

Talk about those things in at least 50% of your content.

These are a few of the top ways that myself & my students are reaching millions of non-followers each month.

STORY INSTRUCTIONS & TIPS:

❤️Follow @misscarolineflett for Instagram secrets

* Start a story with a photo
* Add text and choose the 🔥
* Rotate it upside down, so the orange part is at the top, and expand it to make it huge…way bigger than you think
* Once you get the orange gradient effect, drag it down, so it’s partially covering the photo
* Save the image to your camera roll
* Start a new story with the image you just created
* Add a sticker, choose the camera roll option
* Add the original photo and tap it until it becomes a square
* Add text, choose emojis and search for square.
* Choose the white square frame and drag it into the middle
* Drag the photo on top of the square emoji so you can just see the white outline of the square
* Add a sticker and search Spotify.
* Add the Spotify play sticker and drag it below the photo
* Add a sticker and search Spotify. This time choose the visual audio sticker.
* Add one more sticker and choose music
* Add an audio that suits the vibe of your story and turn off the lyrics
* Add text and type a short message or word using the last font. I used capital letters and added spaces in between each letter.
* Turn the word sideways, expand it to take up the entire height of the story, and drag it to the left.
* Long hold on the word and pull down until it goes to the back layer of your story

IG STORY IDEAS:

* Story Polls: Create fun and interactive polls to gather opinions on topics relevant to your niche or industry.

* This or That: Present your audience with choices related to your interests or industry and encourage them to pick one.

* Trivia or Quizzes: Share interesting trivia or quizzes related to your niche and engage your audience’s curiosity.

* User-Generated Content: Feature user-generated content that showcases your audience using your products or participating in your niche.

* Behind-the-Scenes: Offer a sneak peek into your daily routine, workspace, or creative process.

* Question Stickers: Use the question sticker to invite your audience to ask you anything they’re curious about.

* Sharing Tips: Share quick tips, hacks, or advice related to your area of expertise.

* Challenges: Create fun and light challenges that your audience can participate in and share their results.

* Recommendations: Recommend books, movies, products, or other content that you enjoy.

* Frequently Asked Questions: Address common questions you receive and provide thorough answers.

* Shoutouts: Give shoutouts to other creators, collaborators, or audience members.

🚀1K-200K+ Followers Strategy👇

Update: It’s been a year & a half and I just crossed 1M followers…

And it’s been a crazy ride…

But I wanted to share with you what I did and what worked for me so you can use these strategies to grow your own account.

🔥It’s your time

Post types: I focused almost exclusively on reels. These gave me the most reach & brought in the most new followers.

Post frequency: I posted a lot. 2 reels a day. This helped me hone in on the content that worked best on my account.

Topics: I really tried not to guess about what content my audience wanted to see from me. I researched which worked well in my niche & listened to my audience, & made reels about those topics.

Reels Formats: I tested a variety of reels formats to figure out which ones worked best for my account. For example, short text on screen reels, & longer reels where I used my voice.

Sounds: I used mostly trending audios. I tried to use trending sounds under 10K uses. But the sound that best suited the reel & content message.

Engagement: I asked for engagement whenever & where I could. On screen, in my captions in multiple places, & in my comment section. That includes asking people to follow.

❤️If this has been helpful so far, follow for more

Editing: I tried as much as possible to make my reels engaging. I aimed to get my shorter reels “rewatched” by using interesting transitions, clips timed with my sounds & looping reels.

Repeat: Whenever I had a top performing reel, I tried to repeat the formula or the topic.

Series: I also created multiple series about my top performing topics. This made my account more followable.

Expertise & Value: I made my captions longer & full of value to make sure my audience always got something helpful they could take away from my reels.

I hope this helps you!

History in a bottle! Meet Tiffany Hainesworth, the proud DC native, who made HERstory as the first Black woman to solely own a tequila brand, @tcapritequila.⁠
⁠
After surviving a traumatic car accident in 2012, Tiffany reevaluated her life and pursued her passion for spirits. She began by creating alcohol-infused gourmet treats, which evolved into a deeper ambition: to craft her own tequila. After traveling to Jalisco, Mexico to immerse herself in the tequila-making process, she collaborated with local farmers and distillers to produce her own small batch of tequila .⁠
⁠
Thus, TCapri® Tequila (@tcapritequila) was born, crafted from 100% Blue Weber agave. 👏🏾⁠

Today in History: The Selma to Montgomery March Begins ✊🏾⁠
⁠
On March 21, 1965, thousands of brave souls set out on a 54-mile journey from Selma to Montgomery, demanding the right to vote. Led by Dr. Martin Luther King Jr., this march was a defining moment in the Civil Rights Movement, one that helped pave the way for the Voting Rights Act of 1965.⁠
⁠
The road wasn’t easy, but they marched anyway. They marched for justice, for equality, and for the generations that would come after them.⁠
⁠
Today, we honor their courage and their sacrifice. The fight for our rights didn’t end in 1965, and it’s on us to keep pushing forward. 💪🏾 #BlackHistory⁠

Quote from @vexking’s bestselling book “Good Vibes, Good Life” – available from most major bookstores. Follow @vexking for words of wisdom like the ones below! 🌟⁣
.
“We are not placed on this Earth to endure harm—no matter who it comes from. Love does not ask us to shrink beneath cruelty. Spirituality does not ask us to excuse what wounds and weathers our well-being.
.
Sometimes, the people closest to us—those we are taught to revere without question—are the very ones who cause the deepest harm. Family ties can be sacred, but they are not a free pass for abuse, manipulation, or emotional neglect.
.
Pretending someone’s harmful behaviour is acceptable only extends the cycle of suffering. It teaches us to betray ourselves in the name of loyalty.⁣ You are allowed to draw a sacred line. You are allowed to protect your peace—even if that means creating distance from those who refuse to honour it.⁣
.
Cutting ties with a family member is not a failure of love—it is often the greatest act of self-love. It is the soul’s quiet rebellion against patterns that were never meant to be carried forward.⁣
.
Boundaries provide clarity. They are the prayer that says: “I will no longer sacrifice my wellness for someone else’s unwillingness to love me in the way I deserve.”
.
If you need to walk away from continued harm, do it with no regrets. Grieve if you must, heal at your own pace, but know this—you are not wrong for choosing yourself.⁣
.
You were never meant to suffer endlessly, regardless of whether it’s your “family.” You were meant to live, to expand, to embody love—and sometimes, love means letting go.⁣–#VexKing
Quote taken from @yung_pueblo new book “How to Love Better” which is available to purchase on Amazon.
