Self-care isn’t always soft.⁠
— Sometimes, it looks like distance.⁠
— Sometimes, it means honouring your nervous system and choosing peace over proximity.⁠
⁠
You don’t have to explain why certain people leave you feeling drained. You just have to trust the version of you that feels lighter when they’re not around.⁠
⁠
Protect your peace, even if it means standing alone.⁠
⁠
Leave a 💚 if this resonated with you⁠

You cannot heal what you refuse to face, and you cannot grow while hiding from the truth.⁠
⁠
This is your reminder:⁠
 – Boundaries are necessary, but so is reflection.⁠
 – You can take space and still take ownership.⁠
 – Avoidance is not self-care, it’s self-protection rooted in fear.⁠
 – Real peace requires honesty with yourself first. 🌻⁠
⁠
You are allowed to choose yourself, but not at the expense of becoming someone you don’t recognise. Make space for your feelings. Sit with your discomfort. Say the hard thing with love.⁠
⁠
Because healing isn’t just about protecting your peace, it’s about learning how to live in alignment with it.⁠
⁠
Leave a 💚 if this resonated with you.⁠

I am 30 & i am not ashamed to admit that …. 

1. Reaching the big 3-0 this year was a bit unsettling, to be honest! 😅 I didn’t feel entirely ready to leave my 20s behind, but here I am, embracing this new chapter of life 🎉

2. 🌟 As a BSc Environment Science graduate, I chose not to pursue further studies after seeing my seniors’ job experiences and knowing I didn’t want a traditional 9-to-5 job 🫢. At 19, I started @cats.and.bows as a hobby, driven by my passion for crafting! 🎨✨ I never had a plan B, but I was determined to succeed, no matter how slow the growth would be. Today, I’m proud to say that I’ve built a 7-figure business! 🌟

3. 💼 As a business owner, I’ve learned that I wear multiple hats: artist, marketer, accountant, and more! 🎩 This means working beyond a 40-hour workweek. However, learning to ask for help has been invaluable 🤝.

4. ❤️ Initially, I never thought I’d marry before 30, but life had other plans 🙃. I met my soulmate, @oye_jatiin and got married at 25. I feel blessed to have him by my side 🥰.

5. 💕 Throughout my journey, I’ve realized that friendships may evolve, but true loves stick around 💗. It’s essential to invest your energy in those who reciprocate it.

6. 💪 As a perfectionist in my work and business, I’ve faced challenges, including copycats and doubters 😓. However, I’ve learned that no one can replicate my unique approach.

7. 📈 I’ve also learned that success isn’t just about money; it’s about impact, freedom, and loving what you do ❤️. Don’t compare yourself to others, especially on social media. Remember, success isn’t measured by likes or followers.

8. 🧘‍♀️ Establishing boundaries is crucial in business and life. Remember to receive the same respect you give, and don’t hesitate to part ways with clients who don’t align with your values 👋.

9. 🌈 Owning a business can be challenging, but it’s also incredibly rewarding 🌟. Stay confident, consistent, and grateful, and everything will fall into place with divine timing ⏰!

If any of this resonates with you, drop a ♥️ —l’d love
to hear your thoughts! 🥹

We are shining a light on a side of nursing that's often overlooked: how physically demanding it is to do your job.

Lifting a patient twice your size? No problem.

Walking 16,000 steps over 12 hours, with a 30 minute break? You got this.

Juggling linens, equipment, and emotions? Yes, yes, and yes.

You are the unseen athletes of healthcare. 

The physical endurance and mental toughness to do what you do, every day, should be celebrated!

“I became a yoga teacher because it had such a profound impact on my life,” @villageyoga_santacruz co-founder @sallyshiels shares. “It was a way to give back.”

Staying hydrated with electrolytes is one of the ways Sally takes care of herself so she can show up for her students. But she’s seen the impact salty hydration has on her students, too. Especially after an hour practicing yoga (and sweating) at 104° F.

“Electrolytes are a huge part of being able to enjoy how you feel after yoga. If you’re completely depleted, it can actually have the opposite effect.”

LMNT has been a favorite of her students, too. “We don’t sell a lot of products, but LMNT just flies out the door. Our students love them.”

Want to support your customers or clients with healthy hydration? Check out our Partner Program application at our link in bio — or share this post with a business you think is a good fit ⚡

The sport may be new. But the drive and determination remain the same for @tiaclair1.

“I jumped into HYROX initially for a bit of fun with a mate. And the community, the challenge, it was just something that ignited a fire deep down inside. I realized it was something that I really wanted and needed in my life.”

Competing in HYROX — a circuit-style race combining 5 miles of running interspersed with 8 workout stations — has required a different training formula than competing at the top level of CrossFit. Less strength training, much more running. Learning to rely on a partner after 10+ years of competing solo. And doubling down on her electrolyte intake, with the higher amount she’s sweating during endurance training.

“The new training has been a nice change. It’s been challenging, but I really have enjoyed it. Hydration has also been crucial to my recovery, allowing me to show up day after day.”

Tia has already qualified in two divisions for the HYROX World Championships this coming June, and broke a record in the Pro Women’s Doubles division last month.

HYROX may be new ground. But pouring her heart into the sport? That’s nothing new ⚡

After a challenging childhood being raised by a single mom and getting kicked out by his stepdad at 13, @brentprimus155 turned to street fighting to get out his anger.

Then “one day I woke up and realized I’m gonna end up in prison if I keep doing what I’m doing.” When a friend introduced him to jiu jitsu, “everything changed.”

“Jiu jitsu changed my mindset — there was so much respect and honor and discipline and hard work that went into it.”

20 years later, Brent has made a professional career out of it in the PFL. He prides himself on being the hardest worker in the room — and being the father he didn’t have for his kids.

“There’s no greater motivation than wanting to be a good dad and a role model for them. I think it’s super important that they see me working out, eating healthy, staying hydrated — they’re gonna reflect it.

“I want to be the best version of myself for them.”

Brent has his first fight in the 2025 PFL tournament on Friday, April 18. Good luck, Brent — and Stay Salty ⚡

What fuels @ansel.smo to stay at the front of the pack? Copious amounts of carbs, salty hydration — and bragging rights.

“I got hooked on cycling because of the people. The contrast between comradery and competitiveness is what I love so much about it. We can go hard and push ourselves to the limit… but then we can stop at a cafe and have a latte and a croissant and be best friends.”

As his training (and competitiveness) ramped up, so did his focus on performance and recovery. After experiencing race-stopping cramps in the Phoenix heat, he realized electrolytes were the missing piece.

Low sodium is probably the biggest driver of muscle cramping during exercise. If sodium lost through sweat isn’t replaced — and if the athlete over-hydrates with plain water — fluid balance is disrupted, and cramping is likely.

“I realized that you really need to stay on top of your electrolytes. LMNT has made all the difference. I want to be the friendliest after a ride — but I train to be un-droppable.”

Stay Salty, Ansel ⚡

“The beauty of sign painting is the metamorphosis of a blank wall turning into a beautiful mural,” @justinodaffer shares. But painting a mural 250 feet in the air isn’t just an art — it’s a 10-hour-a-day test of endurance, focus, and sweat.

“I’ve been painting and drawing since I was a kid. I was a kooky boardwalk artist in Venice Beach for a couple years, and worked my way up.”

Now working at @colossalmedia, the largest hand-painting advertising company in the world, Justin’s canvas is the side of a building — and his workdays are much more physically demanding. 10-hour days are common, doing everything from suspending scaffolding and carrying heavy supplies to actually painting the building.

“We’re just out here trying to have fun and create some beautiful artwork.”

I never realized the importance of community until a few years ago.

For me, the beginning years of my legal career left me feeling like I was very much on an island.

I don’t mean to say that I didn’t have support. I have been very lucky to have incredible, incredible friends, a supportive family and the best boyfriend and then husband anyone could ask for, BUT I didn’t have a group where I could openly share my struggles, discuss ways to improve my career, life and business and collaborate with others in a way that felt genuine, empowering and exciting.

And I think a part of me felt like I needed to earn it on my own, to experience and work through the struggle by myself in order to be truly “successful.” Total hogwash.

Community just hits different. And let’s face it, sometimes our loved ones don’t always want to hear about or even understand what we go through in certain phases of our life, whether it’s starting law school, building a business or even becoming a new mom. That is where community comes in.

Since I left Biglaw and went off on my own to start @flourishlawgroup and continue to build @wealthylawyersquad , I discovered the true power of community.

The conversations. The inspiration. And the support to keep going when it feels hard and you feel alone.
One of my favorite communities that I have joined is The Daily Drip.

I am forever grateful to this community for the support they provide to me as a modern South Florida businesswoman.

And, if you tell me there is a photoshoot involved, you better believe I’ll be there! 

Where are you finding your sense of community? I would love to know!

#southfloridabusinesswoman #community #womeninbusiness #womenowned

I am the co-founder of Flourish Law Group, a boutique law firm specializing in trusts and estates, probate and trust administration, and elder law. We are also adding real estate closings and title work as an additional practice area very soon. With over 20 years of experience in tax and trusts and estates, my law partner and I take a hands-on and personalized approach to planning for our clients. We have seen what happens when a person does not have effective estate planning in place and, as a result, our goal is to educate the community and provide top-notch services to make sure families protect their legacies. Our motto is that “we help families flourish at all stages of life.” I am also the founder of The Wealthy Lawyer $quad, a community for law students and new lawyers, which provides programming, education and coaching for the law school process and the first years as an attorney, and focuses on developing confidence, healthy mindset, and strong mental wellbeing and creating a dream career and wealth. In the $quad, we have one coaching program specifically curated for law students called The Law School Success Blueprint and we are launching a separate coaching program curated for new lawyers called The Lawyer Success Blueprint. I am also the host of The Wealthy Lawyer $quad Podcast, where our mission is to provide content that inspires, empowers and supports law students and new lawyers who want to dream big and I strive to shake up the status quo of what it means to be a successful lawyer in today’s world. I’m also a wife, mom, and real estate investor and love to read, workout, travel, try new foods and talk about business and entrepreneurship.
Lauren Klein, Esq., LL.M.
Flourish Law Group

The Lawyer Stories Podcast Episode 187 features Lauren Klein, Founder of modern estate planning law firm + success coach for law students and new lawyers located in Fort Lauderdale, Florida. Lauren shares with us her journey through law school and decision to obtain her LL.M in Taxation at the University of Florida. Lauren started her career by working at a big four accounting firm and then ended up in big law. Eventually, Flourish Law Group was launched and is passionate about bringing exceptional estate planning services to Florida families, navigating the estate planning process, and advising the best ways to protect family, assets, and legacy.

From YouTube royalty to the Actors Guild of America, @mylifeaseva is no stranger to reinvention. One of YouTube’s early stars, she grew up in front of millions - navigating identity, internet fame, and everything in between. Now, she’s stepping into a new rhythm as a DJ, channeling that same unfiltered energy into sound.

In our conversation, she reflects on the chaotic beauty of coming of age online, the weight of digital visibility, opening up for Fred Again and the way fashion has always offered her a kind of language that’s louder than words. 

Now, Eva is turning up the bass with her latest single ‘MONEY’ which has all the ingredients to be a club anthem. This is her uncut: playful, self-aware, and owning every chapter. A story of evolution, and the freedom that comes with living on your own terms.

Was gonna make this caption short and sweet, but snowboarding has brought me so much joy the last few years, and i have to give it a proper shoutout. A lot of you might remember back in the day when i was really into skateboarding and surfing. Board sports made me SO HAPPY, it challenged me in a way that i craved and it was the one hobby i had in my life that made the whole world seem to fade away while i was doing it. But then i got in a bad car accident, i was rear ended by a huge ass truck on the freeway and ended up having to get 3 spine surgeries and 7 other minor surgeries over the years of 2019-2021. I had to completely quit action sports and dancing, and for years, i felt like a big part of my identity was lost and out of my control. 
When i met Olav, he introduced me into snowboarding and it was the first thing i got to try when i finally recovered from years of depression, and all of the pain and the surgeries. It gave me that feeling of challenge, that feeling of “i can be strong” again, and the childlike joy that board sports had given me since i was a just a kid with a Walmart skateboard pushing around Orange County lmao. Snowboarding has given me such amazing friends, taken me to places i never thought I’d go, and given me my confidence back. I can’t tell you enough how much i enjoy this. Thanks @swatch @thenines.cc for letting me a fly on the wall to this insane world you’ve created, and thank YOU SNOWBOARDINGGGG ❤️❄️🏂🌨️🏔️

2025 the year of soft growth, of intentional living. This is the year where you embrace the beauty in the small things, books that expand your mind, friends who nourish your spirit, and the space you make by letting go of anything that dulls your light. Let 2025 be the year you unapologetically choose joy, creativity, and the love you deserve.

Healing isn’t always loud. Sometimes it’s quiet, a small step taken every day, a gentle decision to keep moving forward. And you’ve done that. You’ve survived what you thought would break you. Take a moment to celebrate your resilience. You’ve come so far, give yourself credit for the strength it took to get here.

This is a prayer for your heart, for all the parts of you that feel wounded, lost, or heavy. May you find the healing that you need. May the weight on your shoulders lessen, and may the pain be replaced with peace. You deserve joy, wholeness, and rest from the struggles. I hope you find your way to it soon. 🌻

There is no rulebook that says you need to follow the path everyone else is walking. Your journey is your own, and what you need right now may be vastly different from what the world expects of you. It’s okay to carve your own way, to pause, to create a route that serves your spirit. Being true to yourself is always more valuable than fitting into someone else’s mold. 🌻

Give your energy to those who truly see you. Don’t settle for one-sided connections. Protect your time, because it’s one of the most precious things you have, and it’s too valuable to be wasted. Drop a ❤️ if this resonates.

Knowing where you stand in someone’s life isn't about accepting less; it’s about honoring yourself by seeing things as they are, not as you wish they could be. There is power in clarity. When you understand the role you play for others, you can guard your heart, find peace, and invest in those who truly show up for you. Love doesn’t have to hurt. Let it guide you towards those who care for you, just as much as you care for them.

May 2025 be full of people who match your energy and make you feel valued. But remember, it’s okay to let go of anyone who can't see your worth, because walking away is also a form of love for yourself. Drop a ❤️ if this resonates.

Your gut often knows someone before you do.

Your gut can spot ego, character flaws and negative intentions because your gut instinct doesn’t overlook past lessons like your mind does.

You have to trust your gut when it comes to choosing the people you surround yourself with.

Do you agree? 🙏🏾
You still have time to turn things around. Dedicate December to change, so you can walk into 2025 prepared!

2025 is your time to rise into the fullest version of yourself. Everything you’ve been working for, every silent sacrifice, every night you doubted yourself, it’s all about to come full circle. Success is not just about what’s external, it’s about the internal peace that you’ve fought for too. 🌻

Emotional intelligence is the heart of a good relationship. It’s not just about being loved, it’s about being seen, being heard, and being understood. Love should meet you where you are, and grow alongside you. Find someone who is committed to understanding your heart, not just claiming it. 

Tag someone who needs to see this 🌻

Not everyone in your life will treat you with care, but they all come with lessons. The ones who truly matter are the ones who uplift you, who make you feel seen, who help you become your best self, hold onto them. 

Tag the first person who came to mind. 🌻
